    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 10'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1500' minheight='800' minwidth='1500' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='3' layout-strategy-id='distribute-evenly' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
            <zone fixed-size='744' forceUpdate='true' h='98000' id='5' is-fixed='true' type-v2='text' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='18'>Departmental Diagnostics: Pinpointing the Capacity Bottleneck</run>
                <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>Core Insights &amp; Data Trends:</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Departmental Driver: The top left chart shows that Internal Medicine overwhelmingly drives the hospital&apos;s workload, accounting for 85.5% of all inpatient volume.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Elevated Departmental Stay: The top right chart confirms that Internal Medicine also averages the longest stay at 5.1 days, proving that the capacity pressure is highly localized within this single department.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Specialty Volume Dominance: Drilled down into the specialties, the bottom left chart reveals that Cardiology (600 encounters), Psychiatry (491 encounters), and Pulmonology (447 encounters) completely dominate the volume.

• Outlier Stay Duration: The bottom right chart shows that Pulmonology records a massive Average Length of Stay of 7.4 days. Despite ranking third in patient volume, its prolonged stays consume a disproportionate amount of bed days.</run>
                <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>Impact on Hospital Operations:&#10;</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='12'>•</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Resource Gridlock: Pulmonology and Psychiatry (with a 6.8 day average stay) are keeping beds occupied nearly twice as long as other areas.
</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Bed Consumption: Because Pulmonology keeps patients for an average of 7.4 days, it slows down patient turnover across the wards, directly explaining the persistent bed pressure.</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                <format attr='background-color' value='#f3f4f6' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='21' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='98000' id='20' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
                <zone fixed-size='744' forceUpdate='true' h='98000' id='5' type-v2='text' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='18'>Departmental Diagnostics: Pinpointing the Capacity Bottleneck</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>Core Insights &amp; Data Trends:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Departmental Driver: The top left chart shows that Internal Medicine overwhelmingly drives the hospital&apos;s workload, accounting for 85.5% of all inpatient volume.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Elevated Departmental Stay: The top right chart confirms that Internal Medicine also averages the longest stay at 5.1 days, proving that the capacity pressure is highly localized within this single department.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Specialty Volume Dominance: Drilled down into the specialties, the bottom left chart reveals that Cardiology (600 encounters), Psychiatry (491 encounters), and Pulmonology (447 encounters) completely dominate the volume.

• Outlier Stay Duration: The bottom right chart shows that Pulmonology records a massive Average Length of Stay of 7.4 days. Despite ranking third in patient volume, its prolonged stays consume a disproportionate amount of bed days.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>Impact on Hospital Operations:&#10;</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='12'>•</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Resource Gridlock: Pulmonology and Psychiatry (with a 6.8 day average stay) are keeping beds occupied nearly twice as long as other areas.
</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Bed Consumption: Because Pulmonology keeps patients for an average of 7.4 days, it slows down patient turnover across the wards, directly explaining the persistent bed pressure.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                    <format attr='background-color' value='#f3f4f6' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='8' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zones>
        </devicelayout>
      </devicelayouts>
      <simple-id uuid='{08EC04EA-9C9D-4756-A2F6-7EFBAD69B526}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 11'>
