                <formatted-text>
                  <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='18'>Clinical Analytics: Diagnosis &amp; Readmission Drivers</run>
                  <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>Core Insights &amp; Data Trends:&#10;</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'>• </run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'>Subspecialty Breakdown:</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'> The top charts show Psychiatry&apos;s volume is driven by Substance Use Disorder, and Pulmonology&apos;s volume pressure is driven by Lung Cell Carcinoma.
</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'>• </run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'>Long Stay Drivers:</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'> These two conditions have the hospital&apos;s longest average stays (7.5 days for Substance Use Disorder; 6.9 days for Lung Cell Carcinoma), heavily consuming bed days.
</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'>• </run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'>The Readmission Crisis:</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'> The bottom left chart isolates Pulmonology as the system&apos;s primary driver, accounting for 32.0% of all hospital-wide readmissions.
</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'>• </run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'>The Readmission Bottleneck:</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='12'> The bottom right chart links this to Lung Cell Carcinoma, where a substantial 33.7% readmission rate means over one-third of patients return shortly after discharge.
</run>
                  <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibod' fontsize='14'>Impact on Hospital Operations:&#10;</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold'>• </run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Compounding Bed Pressure:</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> While Psychiatry creates a high initial workload, Pulmonology creates a repeating capacity crisis by combining long stays with frequent readmissions.
</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• </run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Patient Turnover Delays:</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> The 33.7% readmission rate for Lung Cell Carcinoma keeps the same patients cycling through beds, directly causing persistent bed shortages across medical wards.</run>
                </formatted-text>
