    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 13'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1500' minheight='800' minwidth='1500' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='3' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
            <zone fixed-size='744' forceUpdate='true' h='94000' id='5' is-fixed='true' type-v2='text' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='18'>Recommendations: Clinical Leadership</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>&#10;Immediate Actions</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Prioritize Post-Discharge Follow-Up for High-Risk Diagnoses: </run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Strengthen follow-up and care coordination for patients discharged with high-readmission diagnoses, particularly Lung Cell Carcinoma. Earlier follow-up may help identify complications sooner, improve treatment continuity, and reduce avoidable returns to hospital.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;Clinical Review Priorities</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Audit Discharge Readiness Timeline:</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Review the interval between clinical stabilization, discharge readiness, and actual discharge to determine whether prolonged stays are primarily driven by clinical requirements, care coordination challenges, or administrative delays.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Investigate Pulmonology Readmissions:</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Conduct a focused review of Lung Cell Carcinoma readmissions to determine whether treatment-related complications, medication adherence challenges, gaps in follow-up care, disease progression, or other clinical factors are contributing to the elevated readmission rate.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Assess Psychiatry Length of Stay (LOS):</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Review long-stay Psychiatry cases to determine whether the observed average LOS reflects clinical requirements for patient stabilization or opportunities to improve patient flow within the care pathway.</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='background-color' value='#f3f4f6' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='21' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='84000' id='20' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='84000' x='8000' y='8000'>
                <zone fixed-size='744' forceUpdate='true' h='94000' id='5' type-v2='text' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='18'>Recommendations: Clinical Leadership</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>&#10;Immediate Actions</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Prioritize Post-Discharge Follow-Up for High-Risk Diagnoses: </run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Strengthen follow-up and care coordination for patients discharged with high-readmission diagnoses, particularly Lung Cell Carcinoma. Earlier follow-up may help identify complications sooner, improve treatment continuity, and reduce avoidable returns to hospital.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;Clinical Review Priorities</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Audit Discharge Readiness Timeline:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Review the interval between clinical stabilization, discharge readiness, and actual discharge to determine whether prolonged stays are primarily driven by clinical requirements, care coordination challenges, or administrative delays.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Investigate Pulmonology Readmissions:</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Conduct a focused review of Lung Cell Carcinoma readmissions to determine whether treatment-related complications, medication adherence challenges, gaps in follow-up care, disease progression, or other clinical factors are contributing to the elevated readmission rate.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Assess Psychiatry Length of Stay (LOS):</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Review long-stay Psychiatry cases to determine whether the observed average LOS reflects clinical requirements for patient stabilization or opportunities to improve patient flow within the care pathway.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='8' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zones>
        </devicelayout>
      </devicelayouts>
      <simple-id uuid='{4E036990-F1A3-4128-9DE4-FB08E1D23EA6}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 14'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1500' minheight='800' minwidth='1500' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='3' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
            <zone fixed-size='694' forceUpdate='true' h='87750' id='5' is-fixed='true' type-v2='text' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='18'>Recommendations: Operational Leadership</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='tableau semibold' fontsize='14'>&#10;Immediate Actions</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Relieve Ward Pressure Through Step-Down Capacity:</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Expand the use of step-down units and transitional care beds for clinically stable patients. This can help free acute care beds, improve patient throughput, and reduce pressure on overcrowded wards.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Strengthen Workforce Support in High-Burden Areas:</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> High-volume and high-readmission specialties place significant demands on frontline teams. Leadership should review staffing requirements within these areas and deploy additional clinical personnel where necessary to support timely patient management and maintain care quality.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;• </run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Align Bed Allocation with Patient Demand Patterns:</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Review current bed allocation practices to ensure capacity is aligned with specialties and diagnoses generating the greatest demand. Matching resources more closely to patient needs may help reduce bottlenecks and improve flow across the inpatient system.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>&#10;Further Investigation</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• </run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Review the Post-Discharge Patient Journey:</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'> Conduct a detailed review of patient experiences following discharge, including follow-up care, treatment continuity, treatment-related complications, medication access, and community-based support services. Understanding these factors will help identify potential drivers of readmissions and inform targeted interventions.</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='background-color' value='#f3f4f6' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
