                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>While the dataset provides excellent visibility into Gross Billed Amount and Net Revenue, it lacks internal cost accounting metrics.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Without specific data on daily bed maintenance costs or insurance readmission penalty structures, we cannot calculatethe exact net profit margins or precise financial loss per extended stay.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>Lack of Patient Acuity and Clinical Severity Metrics:</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>The data does not include clinical acuity scores, such as psychiatric stabilization stages or cancer staging for Lung Cell Carcinoma.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Therefore, the analysis cannot definitively separate whether a 7.5-day average stay in Psychiatry is driven purely by operational workflow delays or by highly complex, medically necessary stabilization requirements</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>No Post-Discharge Care Tracking:</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='12'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Because we lack tracking data on outpatient medication adherence, clinic follow-ups, or community support access, we are unable to determine whether these external root causes are driving the 33.7% Pulmonology readmission rate.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
