    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 9'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1500' minheight='800' minwidth='1500' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='3' layout-strategy-id='distribute-evenly' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
            <zone fixed-size='744' forceUpdate='true' h='98000' id='5' is-fixed='true' type-v2='text' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='18'>Operational Diagnostics: Volume vs. Capacity Pressures</run>
                <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>•Persistent Bed Occupancy Pressure: </run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>The bottom trend line demonstrates that the Average Length of Stay (ALOS) remains consistently elevated throughout the entire year, frequently peaking between 5.1 and 5.6 days (such as in March, May,August, and October) completely independent of seasonal volume drops.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Prolonged Inpatient Stays: This sustained high ALOS validates executive concerns regarding prolonged inpatient stays.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Because the stay duration stays high even when volume drops (like in March and August), this isolates the issue to internal operational factors, which we will break down in the following sections to pinpoint the exact capacity bottleneck.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>Impact on Hospital Operations:</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• High Workload: 1,907 total encounters resulted in 9,061 total bed days, confirming that departments are operating under immense physical pressure.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Bed Gridlock: A 4.7-day average stay ties up beds, delays turnover, and creates financial strain by blocking new admissions.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Readmission Penalty: A 9.7% readmission rate means nearly 10 out of 100 patients return, draining clinical resources and increasing financial penalties.</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='background-color' value='#f3f4f6' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='21' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='84000' id='20' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='84000' x='8000' y='8000'>
                <zone fixed-size='744' forceUpdate='true' h='98000' id='5' type-v2='text' w='98934' x='533' y='1000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='18'>Operational Diagnostics: Volume vs. Capacity Pressures</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>•Persistent Bed Occupancy Pressure: </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>The bottom trend line demonstrates that the Average Length of Stay (ALOS) remains consistently elevated throughout the entire year, frequently peaking between 5.1 and 5.6 days (such as in March, May,August, and October) completely independent of seasonal volume drops.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Prolonged Inpatient Stays: This sustained high ALOS validates executive concerns regarding prolonged inpatient stays.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>Because the stay duration stays high even when volume drops (like in March and August), this isolates the issue to internal operational factors, which we will break down in the following sections to pinpoint the exact capacity bottleneck.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='14'>Impact on Hospital Operations:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• High Workload: 1,907 total encounters resulted in 9,061 total bed days, confirming that departments are operating under immense physical pressure.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Bed Gridlock: A 4.7-day average stay ties up beds, delays turnover, and creates financial strain by blocking new admissions.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Semibold' fontsize='12'>• Readmission Penalty: A 9.7% readmission rate means nearly 10 out of 100 patients return, draining clinical resources and increasing financial penalties.</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='8' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zones>
        </devicelayout>
      </devicelayouts>
      <simple-id uuid='{46635C68-0731-4682-9507-66AC5F354EF5}' />
    </dashboard>
